{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/post/introducing-codesandbox-search-patron-much-more","webpackCompilationHash":"43a07f76784e304bf1a0","result":{"data":{"blogPost":{"fields":{"authors":["Ives van Hoorne"],"date":"2017-07-21T00:00:00.000Z","description":"Introducing the new features built in July. Includes Sandbox Tagging, Search, CodeSandbox Patron, dedicated preferences, private sandboxes, ...","photo":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/587016?s=460&v=4","slug":"introducing-codesandbox-search-patron-much-more","title":"Introducing CodeSandbox Search, Patron & much more!"},"frontmatter":{"banner":{"publicURL":"/static/banner-8e60e7ee38c80321ab15bea8a8770d01.png"}},"html":"<p>It has been only 3 weeks since <a href=\"https://codesandbox.io\">our</a> last article\n'<a href=\"/post/the-future-of-codesandbox\">The Future of CodeSandbox</a>' has been\nreleased. We haven't stopped working in the meantime and are proud to release\nour biggest update yet today! I wanted to dedicate a separate post for this\nupdate, since it wouldn't fit in a single tweet (or even two for that matter).\nIt's good to keep everyone posted regularly on all progress and that's why we're\nstarting a monthly post, explaining what big features have been built and what\nwe will build.</p>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"what-has-been-built\"><a href=\"#what-has-been-built\" aria-label=\"what has been built permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What has been built</h2>\n<p>This update is much bigger than I initially planned. I first just wanted to\nbuild search, but then I realized that people want private sandboxes if there's\nsearch, so I built pricing, but then I realized that users need to be able to\nupdate their payment info, so I built dedicated preferences. Without further\nado, let's look at the new features in detail!</p>\n<h4 id=\"sandbox-tagging\"><a href=\"#sandbox-tagging\" aria-label=\"sandbox tagging permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Sandbox Tagging</h4>\n<p><img src=\"/f6eb9fcb8b53973ece547272f70de9a0/0.gif\"></p>\n<p>It's now possible to tag sandboxes, so you're able to sort and group them based\non given tags. This is especially useful with the next feature.</p>\n<h4 id=\"search\"><a href=\"#search\" aria-label=\"search permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"https://codesandbox.io/search\">Search</a></h4>\n<p>Yes! I'm really excited for this feature. We now have search powered by\n<a href=\"https://algolia.com\">Algolia</a>. It's insanely fast, I was never able to exceed\nthe 2ms in search time with 22,000 sandboxes. Integration was also much easier\nthan I expected, it took me two days to do the backend and the frontend.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 740px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/a987b/1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.29166666666667%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Notice the blue highlights? Other templates will have other highlights in the future (eg. Preact will be purple)\"\n        title=\"Notice the blue highlights? Other templates will have other highlights in the future (eg. Preact will be purple)\"\n        src=\"/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/bcf2d/1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/d5c4a/1.png 185w,\n/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/04e89/1.png 370w,\n/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/bcf2d/1.png 740w,\n/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/dbb75/1.png 1110w,\n/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/a808b/1.png 1480w,\n/static/9f06e86dc7856e895a3e2dffb9deacc7/a987b/1.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Search is really useful when you're searching for examples or inspiration. Do\nyou need help with\n<a href=\"https://github.com/ReactTraining/react-router/tree/master/packages/react-router-dom\"><code class=\"language-text\">react-router-dom</code></a>\nand\n<a href=\"https://github.com/reactjs/react-transition-group\"><code class=\"language-text\">react-transition-group</code></a>?\nWell, now you can just filter on those dependencies and check the sandboxes out.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/bba3562507e4bba03d35de77b505f28b/2.gif\"></p>\n<p>Not only is this useful for users, library authors now also have a higher\nvisibility when users are searching for libraries. Search is also where tags\nshine, since you can also filter on tags.</p>\n<p>The search isn't fully done yet, I also want to add 'Popular Sandboxes', 'Top of\nthis week' and 'Top of this month' to increase discoverability.</p>\n<h4 id=\"codesandbox-patron\"><a href=\"#codesandbox-patron\" aria-label=\"codesandbox patron permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a><a href=\"https://codesandbox.io/patron\">CodeSandbox Patron</a></h4>\n<p>You can now support CodeSandbox by becoming a Patron! You get a badge based on\nthe amount you donate per month, which will be shown on your profile page. You\ncan hide the badge in your preferences. The income will go to server costs and\nfurther expenses of CodeSandbox.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/a6fd2a8a09a15059a240b0277d9b34ad/3.gif\"></p>\n<p>We don't want to split features between Patrons and free users, that's why\nmostly limits are lifted when you are a Patron. As you can see you can pay what\nyou want, this goes from $5 to $∞. We handle all payments through\n<a href=\"https://stripe.com\">Stripe</a>, and we're also working on\n<a href=\"https://paypal.com\">PayPal</a> integration. You can find the patron page\n<a href=\"https://codesandbox.io/patron\">here</a>.</p>\n<h4 id=\"private-sandboxes\"><a href=\"#private-sandboxes\" aria-label=\"private sandboxes permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Private Sandboxes</h4>\n<p>As a Patron you can make your sandboxes either private or unlisted. Unlisted\nsandboxes are not indexed, thus others can only find them if they have the right\nURL. Private sandboxes are only viewable by you. You can find the privacy\noptions under 'Sandbox Actions'.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 253px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6aa92f95fc5b7733af2cbe1593f4d80d/1df96/4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 86.56126482213438%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"4\"\n        title=\"4\"\n        src=\"/static/6aa92f95fc5b7733af2cbe1593f4d80d/1df96/4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6aa92f95fc5b7733af2cbe1593f4d80d/d5c4a/4.png 185w,\n/static/6aa92f95fc5b7733af2cbe1593f4d80d/1df96/4.png 253w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 253px) 100vw, 253px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>You can view your private and unlisted sandboxes on your own profile, but when\nothers see your profile they can't see these sandboxes.</p>\n<h4 id=\"dedicated-preferences\"><a href=\"#dedicated-preferences\" aria-label=\"dedicated preferences permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Dedicated Preferences</h4>\n<p>We now have a preferences modal with a fancy animation!</p>\n<p><img src=\"/1469c14788fe9bc1b2f7033b28734953/5.gif\"></p>\n<p>This opens up the possibility to have advanced preferences, like\n<a href=\"https://github.com/eslint/eslint\">ESLint</a> config, custom\n<a href=\"https://github.com/prettier/prettier\">Prettier</a> config and customized theming.\nWe will also include more preferences. The design of the preferences modal is\ninspired by <a href=\"https://discordapp.com\">Discord</a> and Stripe.</p>\n<h4 id=\"achievement-badges\"><a href=\"#achievement-badges\" aria-label=\"achievement badges permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Achievement Badges</h4>\n<p>We will gradually add achievement badges to CodeSandbox, as a sort of reward for\nyour support and usage. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/bazzjuh\">Bas Buursma</a> has put a lot\nof effort in the design of the badges, and they turned out really beautiful!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 740px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/9c46e/6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.4%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"6\"\n        title=\"6\"\n        src=\"/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/bcf2d/6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/d5c4a/6.png 185w,\n/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/04e89/6.png 370w,\n/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/bcf2d/6.png 740w,\n/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/dbb75/6.png 1110w,\n/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/a808b/6.png 1480w,\n/static/53d7ed293795d519615b83a285bb1b7c/9c46e/6.png 4000w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Currently we have 4 badges, but we promised another one in the last post. In the\nlast post I wrote that we had a reward for all early birds of CodeSandbox,\nthat's why the first 2,000 users of CodeSandbox will receive an early bird\nbadge! This badge is still in the making.</p>\n<p>Throughout the coming months we'll build more badges and a separate badges page.</p>\n<h4 id=\"terms-of-service\"><a href=\"#terms-of-service\" aria-label=\"terms of service permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Terms of Service</h4>\n<p>Hosting user created content is legally quite tricky. A Terms of Service and a\nPrivacy Policy were long due and we've put a lot of time in writing one. You can\nread it <a href=\"https://codesandbox.io/legal\">here</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"what-will-come\"><a href=\"#what-will-come\" aria-label=\"what will come permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What will come</h2>\n<p>Last month was very focused on discoverability of the sandboxes. The coming\nmonth we will focus more on the editor and the preview functionality. I have 2\nholidays in August (I'm lucky), so this could become a sprint of two months\ninstead of one.</p>\n<h4 id=\"extension--custom-renderer-support\"><a href=\"#extension--custom-renderer-support\" aria-label=\"extension  custom renderer support permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Extension &#x26; Custom Renderer Support</h4>\n<p>I've laid some thinking groundworks on support for custom extensions and\nrenderers. The idea is that library authors can build devtools and custom\nrenderers integrated with CodeSandbox.</p>\n<p>Imagine you have a state management library, then you should be able to open a\ncustom view like in\n<a href=\"https://mattiamanzati.github.io/mobx-state-tree-playground\">mobx-state-tree-playground</a>\nto inspect state and actions. Or imagine you have\n<a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/jest\">Jest</a> tests, then it would be great if you\ncan visually see your tests running in a custom view. And it would also be great\nif you can finally open a console view.</p>\n<p>The idea is that you can write a custom extension for CodeSandbox, where you can\nspecify when the extension is activated, how modules are evaluated and what\nshould be rendered. You can then add the extension via a PR to the main\ncodebase.</p>\n<h4 id=\"templates-support\"><a href=\"#templates-support\" aria-label=\"templates support permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Templates Support</h4>\n<p>We now have compatibility with\n<a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app\"><code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code></a> templates,\nand we want to extend this to other templates. This feature will be tightly\nconnected to the custom renderer support, because both projects will be put in a\ncomplete rewrite of the sandbox. We're not planning to support ejecting in this\nsprint, that work won't fit in one sprint.</p>\n<h4 id=\"the-internals-of-codesandbox\"><a href=\"#the-internals-of-codesandbox\" aria-label=\"the internals of codesandbox permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The Internals of CodeSandbox</h4>\n<p>A couple days ago I sent out a tweet gauging the interest in a post about how\nCodeSandbox is built:</p>\n<p><blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-dnt=\"true\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Is anyone interested in a Medium post about how CodeSandbox works? <br /><br />There is far more than the web app that keeps it running 🤓. <a href=\"https://t.co/3xUV6NPA9X\">pic.twitter.com/3xUV6NPA9X</a></p>&mdash; Ives van Hoorne (@CompuIves) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CompuIves/status/885197233519570947\">July 12, 2017</a></blockquote></p>\n<p>The response was really positive and better than I expected. I'm motivated to\nstart writing about the internals of CodeSandbox and how different parts work\ntogether soon.</p>\n</section>\n<section>\n<h2 id=\"thanks\"><a href=\"#thanks\" aria-label=\"thanks permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Thanks</h2>\n<p>Remember, <a href=\"https://github.com/codesandbox/codesandbox-client\">we're</a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/codesandbox/codesandbox-importers/tree/master/packages/cli\">open</a>\n<a href=\"https://github.com/codesandbox/codesandbox-importers/tree/master/packages/git-extractor\">source</a>\n(partly)! I'd like to give a special thanks for our new contributors of the past\nmonth. ❤️</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 510px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/de78428e83730e72ff2ba78cc7be1d1b/bbeb6/7.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 33.13725490196078%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"7\"\n        title=\"7\"\n        src=\"/static/de78428e83730e72ff2ba78cc7be1d1b/bbeb6/7.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/de78428e83730e72ff2ba78cc7be1d1b/d5c4a/7.png 185w,\n/static/de78428e83730e72ff2ba78cc7be1d1b/04e89/7.png 370w,\n/static/de78428e83730e72ff2ba78cc7be1d1b/bbeb6/7.png 510w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 510px) 100vw, 510px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Also a BIG thanks to everyone else helping out by talking about and using\nCodeSandbox, we're really amazed by your positive response and support.</p>\n<p>You can always contact us through <a href=\"https://twitter.com/CompuIves\">my Twitter</a> or\nby emailing us at hello@codesandbox.io. Don't hesitate to say hi 😃.</p>\n</section>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"id":"1e938375-0fa8-50e1-a427-939eb78c0a8d"}}}